cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the numerical decomposition of polynomial systems into irreducible factors using path tracking techniques. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on solution sets of high degrees. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is relevant as the paper uses monodromy and linear trace concepts to break up the solution set. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with the computation of loops around singularities. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the parallel implementation of the algorithm and synchronization issues.
